data.content:
**In .NET 11, sync I/O on the Cosmos DB provider is fully removed — no opt-in exists anymore.** Your `.ToList()`, `.First()`, `.Count()`, and `.SaveChanges()` calls will **always throw** at runtime, regardless of configuration.

Convert everything to async:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

The `async` change will ripple up to all callers, so you'll need to make the calling code async as well (controllers, services, etc.). There is no workaround — the Cosmos DB SDK is async-only and EF Core 11 no longer wraps it in sync-over-async.
